{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06561ec96401866e27f87485890f61c6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nWhen a `.jsonl` file is deleted before `claude_consult`, the orphan recovery path runs:\n\n---\n\n**1. `consultService.consult()`** (`src/consult.ts:52`) — acquires `cost:` project lock, calls `resolveRoute()`\n\n**2. `resolveRoute()`** (`src/consult.ts:249`) — two branches:\n\n**Explicit `session_id` provided** (`src/consult.ts:251-291`):\n- Session found in SQLite; project ownership verified\n- `sessionFileExists(claude_session_id)` called (`src/claude.ts:104-122`) — checks `~/.claude/sessions/{id}.json`, `sessions/{id}.jsonl`, and 3-level deep search in `~/.claude/projects`\n- **File missing** → `db.markSessionOrphaned(session.id)` (`src/db.ts:518-530`): status set to `orphaned`, `orphan_recovery` event logged\n- Returns `RouteResolution` with `selectedSession = null`, `bootstrapContext = buildBootstrapContext(oldView, \"orphaned\")`, `wasOrphanRecovery = true`\n\n**Null `session_id` (auto-route)** (`src/consult.ts:294-321`):\n- `listMatchCandidates` fetches active+dormant sessions\n- `sessionFileExists` checked on each candidate before reuse — orphaned sessions skipped silently\n- Orphaned exact-topic match is also detected and marked orphaned before scoring\n\n**3. `invokeWithRouteLock()`** (`src/consult.ts:97-115`) — since `selectedSession = null`, skips the per-session lock, goes straight to `invokeClaude()`\n\n**4. `invokeClaude()`** (`src/consult.ts:117`):\n- Bootstrap context (compact registry snapshot: topic, summary, decisions, files, tags, aliases) injected via `buildBootstrapContext()`\n- `claude.runPrompt(prompt)` called **without `--resume`** — new Claude session created\n- New `claude_session_id` stored in SQLite\n- Event `new_session` logged with `was_orphan_recovery = true`\n\n---\n\n**Outcome**: Deleted session remains in SQLite as `orphaned` historical record; new session created; old compact metadata transferred as bootstrap context so no architectural memory is lost. `was_orphan_recovery = true` in `session_events` gives full observability."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":133707,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1bc568d1-5a5f-4314-b4be-00aca006f5e1","uuid":"59a4a334-5275-41d6-8361-27b996e2dd44"}
